cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the security and privacy aspects of P2P multimedia content distribution, which falls under the scope of computer security (cs.CR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed system also involves efficient distribution of large-sized content, which could be related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of collusion-resistant codes for fingerprinting is a technique from information theory (cs.IT) which is also mentioned in the paper.
